                <fr:title text="A working OCaml 5 installation">A working OCaml 5 installation</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Requirement</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:p><fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-005P.xml" title="Forester › release notes" addr="//forester/jms-005P" type="local">Forester</fr:link> is a tool written in the <fr:link href="https://www.ocaml.org/" type="external">OCaml</fr:link> programming language, and makes use of the latest features of OCaml 5. Most users should install <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-005P.xml" title="Forester › release notes" addr="//forester/jms-005P" type="local">Forester</fr:link> through OCaml's <fr:link href="https://opam.ocaml.org/" type="external">opam</fr:link> package manager; instructions to install opam and OCaml simultaneously can be found <fr:link href="https://opam.ocaml.org/" type="external">here</fr:link>.</fr:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
